The theoretical densities of the HfMoTaTiZr and HfMoNbTaTiZr alloys are 10.21 g/cm 3 and 9.95 g/cm 3 , respectively. These values are also close to the experimental values, d HfMoTaTiZr ¼ 10.24 g/cm 3 and d HfMoNbTaTiZr ¼ 9.97 g/cm 3 . Moreover, a fracture strain of 12% is successfully retained in the HfMoNbTaTiZr alloy at room temperature.
The yield strength of the HfMoTaTiZr alloy at RT is 1600 MPa. The alloy shows its peak strength of 1743 MPa at ε ¼ 3%, and subsequently fails at ε ¼ 4%.
The yield strength of the HfMoNbTaTiZr alloy at RT is 1512 MPa. The peak strength of this alloy occurring at ε ¼ 11% is 1828 MPa. The maximum compression strain is 12%.
Because of its better combination of strength and plasticity, HfMoNbTaTiZr is even better than HfMoTaTiZr.

The compression yield strengths of the HfMoTaTiZr alloy at RT, 800, 1000, and 1200 C are 1600, 1045, 855, and 339 MPa, respectively. The fracture strain of the HfMoTaTiZr alloy is 4% at RT.
